<br>
You can find these in the Jugg area, but also in Skyfire (found them all in Skyfire actually). Dragons commonly drop these spells as well. <br>
<br>
I usually charge 2k for the spells. The only one I would consider charging more than 2k for is Mask, since out of the bunch it is the most useful. <br>
<br>
Form of the Hunter is quite useless. So is Entrapping Root. Try not to pay too much for these.<br>
<br>
Legacy of Thorn is also psuedo-useless -- it puts a 24 pt damage shield on your group, but the mage spell Boon of Immolation(53, I think) puts a 25 pt damage shield up. It's good if you don't have a mage, but otherwise, it's fairly unused.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udreth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dreth1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/5/01 7:52:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2297.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mask/Form Hunter, Legacy of Thorn, Entrapping root</span><hr size=1> Thanks for info.<br>
